headline: Syntis Bio Closes $38 Million Financing to Accelerate Oral Therapies for Obesity and Rare Diseases
summary: BOSTON, July 01, 2025--Syntis Bio, Inc. (Syntis), a clinical-stage biopharmaceutical company revolutionizing oral therapies for obesity, diabetes and rare diseases, announced today the close of a $33 million oversubscribed Series A financing. Cerberus Ventures led the round, with participation from new investors Mansueto Investments, Woori Venture Partners and Apollo Labs. Founding investors BOLD Capital Partners, W. R.
